	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A senator of uncertain date, probably early first century. His accuser, L. Cossinius of Tibur, won Roman citizenship by his condemnation, and Cossinius' son was a prominent equestrian contemporary of Cicero (Cic. Balb. 53). See Badian, Gnomon 33, 1961, 493.[43]\n" .
